ExecDesc.value: Nullsoft Winamp AVI Stream Count Integer Overflow

EngDesc.value: A buffer overflow vulnerability exists in Winamp. The vulnerability is due to an integer overflow when a stream count from an AVI file is used in a buffer size calculation. A remote unauthenticated attacker can exploit this vulnerability by enticing a target user to open a crafted AVI file. A successful exploitation attempt may result in the execution of arbitrary code in the security context of the target user.
